  • Terminally Deprecated Elements
    Element
    Description
    io.ebean.config.DatabaseConfig.getClasses()
    - migrate to DatabaseConfig.classes().
    io.ebean.config.DatabaseConfig.isAutoLoadModuleInfo()
    - migrate to DatabaseConfig.isLoadModuleInfo().
    io.ebean.DatabaseBuilder.Settings.getClasses()
    - migrate to DatabaseBuilder.Settings.classes().

    Sorry if returning Set rather than List breaks code but it feels safer to do that than a subtle change to return a shallow copy which you will not detect.

    io.ebean.DatabaseBuilder.Settings.isAutoLoadModuleInfo()
    - migrate to DatabaseBuilder.Settings.isLoadModuleInfo().
    io.ebean.event.ServletContextListener
    io.ebean.ExpressionList.delete(Transaction)
    migrate to ExpressionList.usingTransaction(Transaction) then delete().

    Execute as a delete query deleting the 'root level' beans that match the predicates in the query.

    Note that if the query includes joins then the generated delete statement may not be optimal depending on the database platform.

    io.ebean.ExpressionList.filterMany(String, String, Object...)
    for removal - migrate to ExpressionList.filterManyRaw(String, String, Object...).

    Add filter expressions to the many property. 

    

   DB.find(Customer.class)
   .where()
   .eq("name", "Rob")
   .filterMany("orders", "status = ?", Status.NEW)
   .findList();
    io.ebean.ExpressionList.order()
    migrate to ExpressionList.orderBy().
    io.ebean.ExpressionList.order(String)
    migrate to ExpressionList.orderBy(String)
    io.ebean.ExpressionList.update(Transaction)
    migrate to ExpressionList.usingTransaction(Transaction) then update().

    Execute as a update query with the given transaction.

    io.ebean.Query.delete(Transaction)
    migrate to QueryBuilder.usingTransaction(Transaction) then delete().

    Execute as a delete query returning the number of rows deleted using the given transaction.

    Note that if the query includes joins then the generated delete statement may not be optimal depending on the database platform.

    io.ebean.Query.order()
    migrate to Query.orderBy().
    io.ebean.Query.order(String)
    migrate to Query.orderBy().
    io.ebean.Query.setOrder(OrderBy<T>)
    migrate to QueryBuilder.setOrderBy(OrderBy).
    io.ebean.Query.update(Transaction)
    migrate to QueryBuilder.usingTransaction(Transaction) then update().

    Execute the UpdateQuery returning the number of rows updated using the given transaction.
